-- Brazil Coffee Exports Fall to 1.95 Million Bags in January
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-02-01T17:50:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/brazil-coffee-exports-fall-to-1-95-million-bags-in-january.html
Coffee exports from  Brazil , the
world’s largest producer and shipper, fell 25 percent in January
from a year earlier, Brazil’s Trade Ministry said.  Shipments dropped to 1.95 million bags from 2.59 million
bags a year ago, the ministry said today in a report on its
website. A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms (132 pounds).  The average export price was $286.50 a bag last month, up
from $217.50 a year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
